    "image_count": 2,
    "description": "When Trump began openly pushing mid-decade redistricting\u2014starting in Texas, where he insisted Republicans were \u201centitled\u201d to more seats\u2014he was upending the game board and unilaterally changing the rules of the game, in the middle of the game. Maps would be drawn not after the census, not through some pretense of fairness, but whenever power demanded it. And Republicans dutifully followed. Missouri, North Carolina, Ohio. The message spread quickly: redraw now, ask questions never.",
    "title": "Trump's Attack Dogs"
  },
